00:39:42,820 --> 00:39:44,540
Just another plate at the table.

861
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:47,180
I'm ok with it.

862
00:39:47,540 --> 00:39:49,140
Alright, your call.

863
00:39:49,140 --> 00:39:50,940
(Nova Bakery)

864
00:39:50,940 --> 00:39:51,780
Come.

865
00:39:57,660 --> 00:40:00,980
(Early 2000)

866
00:40:03,340 --> 00:40:06,020
Mom, I really don't want to go back.

867
00:40:06,980 --> 00:40:08,980
Still, you have to.

868
00:40:09,380 --> 00:40:12,060
A married daughter can't be taken back.

869
00:40:12,980 --> 00:40:15,140
How can you live with your mom?

870
00:40:15,180 --> 00:40:16,780
But Jiali lives with you.

871
00:40:18,620 --> 00:40:19,780
She has no mother-in-law.

872
00:40:19,780 --> 00:40:21,180
No one will blame her.

873
00:40:21,780 --> 00:40:23,420
Mom, I'm worried about you.

874
00:40:23,740 --> 00:40:25,580
Who's going to take care of you?

875
00:40:25,580 --> 00:40:27,580
I worry about every bite you take.

876
00:40:29,700 --> 00:40:31,180
You're making a fuss.

877
00:40:51,180 --> 00:40:52,580
No wonder it's cold inside.

878
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:54,860
Why did you open the door so wide?

879
00:40:54,980 --> 00:40:57,020
Just airing the room. I'll close it later.

880
00:40:57,180 --> 00:40:59,580
Why did you take my Asparagus Fern out?

881
00:41:00,180 --> 00:41:01,740
It wasn't me. It was Jiaxi.

882
00:41:03,660 --> 00:41:04,620
You didn't even water it.

883
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:07,980
You've been keeping it for years.

884
00:41:07,980 --> 00:41:10,020
Don't you know the "soak and dry" rule?

885
00:41:10,780 --> 00:41:11,860
It's drying out.

886
00:41:17,980 --> 00:41:19,780
Isn't it just fine?

887
00:41:22,780 --> 00:41:24,020
(Stride across the new century)

888
00:41:24,020 --> 00:41:25,620
One more. Two more.

889
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:27,700
And this.

890
00:41:27,700 --> 00:41:30,180
(Usher in the millennium)

891
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:32,140
Here, two yuan.

892
00:41:32,420 --> 00:41:34,220
- I'll tie it for you.
- No need, I'll do it.

893
00:41:37,780 --> 00:41:38,940
Now it's good.

894
00:41:40,540 --> 00:41:41,620
I'll grab some melon seeds. Bye.

895
00:41:41,620 --> 00:41:42,460
Ok.

896
00:41:42,540 --> 00:41:43,420
Come back again.

897
00:41:43,420 --> 00:41:44,260
Miss!

898
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:45,460
Excuse me,

899
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:47,060
is there any cheap and good hotel

900
00:41:47,060 --> 00:41:49,540
in your neighborhood?

901
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:52,060
There's Nova Hotel up ahead,

902
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:54,220
and then Longyuan Hotel on the right.

903
00:41:54,740 --> 00:41:55,820
Not a fancy hotel.

904
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,540
I don't have much money.

905
00:41:57,900 --> 00:42:01,060
Just a cheap one with hot water.

906
00:42:01,060 --> 00:42:02,300
There's nothing like that around here.

907
00:42:04,500 --> 00:42:06,260
Why is it so hard to find a small hotel

908
00:42:06,460 --> 00:42:08,300
in such a big place?

909
00:42:08,820 --> 00:42:09,660
Thanks.

910
00:42:29,820 --> 00:42:30,660
Honey.

911
00:42:31,700 --> 00:42:34,020
Why don't we open a hotel?

912
00:42:34,860 --> 00:42:35,700
Hotel?

913
00:42:37,100 --> 00:42:38,100
What kind of hotel?

914
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:39,380
One of those

915
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:40,860
affordable.

916
00:42:41,300 --> 00:42:42,500
I don't think

917
00:42:42,940 --> 00:42:44,300
there are many of those hotels.

918
00:42:46,540 --> 00:42:47,380
Then,

919
00:42:48,140 --> 00:42:49,660
we'll have to rent a place.

920
00:42:49,700 --> 00:42:52,060
Also, the location is very important.

921
00:42:52,060 --> 00:42:52,900
Yes,

922
00:42:53,020 --> 00:42:54,220
the location matters.

923
00:42:57,260 --> 00:42:58,340
Opening a hotel requires

924
00:42:58,340 --> 00:43:00,780
more investment than a bathhouse, right?

